   Career Guidance - 6 Game-Changing Job Search Strategies

6 Game-Changing Job Search Strategies

   By [72]Scott Dockweiler

   We know, you’re probably spending this afternoon lounging on the couch
   with delicious snacks [73]while watching your favorite sports team. And
   while we certainly recommend enjoying your relaxing weekend afternoon,
   why not use the commercial breaks to move your job search forward?

   For an easy transition, start with these six smart job search
   strategies borrowed from your favorite games and sports. From learning
   how to be a boomerang in your career to building up a strong team of
   connections, include these tips in your game plan, and you’ll see
   success in no time.
     __________________________________________________________________

Can’t get enough fun and games? Check out these entertainment companies that
are hiring!
     __________________________________________________________________

Infographic courtesy of [74]CareerShift. Photo of [75]football player
courtesy of Shutterstock.

   Career Guidance

About The Author

   Scott Dockweiler crafts witty headlines, writes fun articles, and
   generally lends a hand to the editorial team at The Daily Muse. When
   he’s not Musing, he’s trying to get his acting career off the ground
   and racking up Delta Airlines frequent flier miles between NYC and LA.
   You won’t find him on Twitter—yet.
